# Product Requirements Document (PRD): PickLT Client Mobile App

## Product Overview

PickLT is a European-based mobile and web application designed to simplify the process of moving items, properties, and belongings for anyone relocating — whether from apartments, offices, or businesses — from one area or building to another. This PRD covers the **client-facing mobile application** built with React Native and Expo, targeting the person requesting the move (not the driver/mover).

## Goals & Objectives

- Provide a frictionless, on-demand and scheduled moving service experience for clients.
- Ensure secure and verified user access via email/Google authentication plus mandatory phone OTP verification.
- Allow users to initiate instant or scheduled move requests with clear configuration options.
- Keep users informed of their move statuses through an intuitive dashboard.
- Deliver a polished, Figma-faithful UI using Claude Code + Figma MCP for design-to-code translation.

## Target Users

- Individuals relocating apartments or personal belongings within Europe.
- Offices and businesses moving equipment, furniture, or inventory between locations.
- Anyone who needs items picked up from one location and delivered to another.

## Core Features

### 1. Onboarding & Splash
- Branded splash screen on app launch.
- Carousel-style onboarding screens introducing the app's value proposition (instant moves, scheduled moves).
- Options to sign up with email, sign up with Google, or sign in (for returning users).
- First-time users flow through onboarding; returning users with valid tokens bypass to Home.

### 2. User Authentication
- **Sign Up:** Custom email/password or Google SSO.
- **Mandatory Phone Verification:** Regardless of sign-up method, every user must verify their phone number via SMS OTP (4–6 digits).
- **Post-Signup Profile Confirmation:** New users are routed to a settings/profile page to confirm their name and personal details. This is important because Google auth may not reflect a user's real name, and real names are recommended for the service.
- **Sign In:** Email/password login for returning users with the same OTP flow if needed.

### 3. Password Change / Recovery
- User taps "Forgot Password" from the login screen.
- User selects OTP delivery method: Email or Phone number.
- User receives OTP, enters it, then sets a new password.
- Redirects back to login after successful password change.

### 4. Home Dashboard
- **Move Request Form:** A prominent form at the top of the home screen allowing users to:
  - Toggle between **Instant** and **Scheduled** move categories.
  - Enter **Pickup Location** and **Drop-off Location**.
  - Select **Move Type**: Light, Regular, or Premium.
  - Submit to initiate the move request process.
- **Move Status Dashboard:** Below the form, a set of category tabs (e.g., Pending, In Transit, Completed) displaying move request cards.
- **Move Cards:** Compact cards showing minimal move details (date, locations, status tag). Tapping a card navigates to the Move Details screen.

### 5. Move Details
- Full detail view of a selected move request.
- Displays all move information: pickup/drop-off addresses, move type, status, date/time, and any additional notes.

### 6. Bottom Navigation Bar
- Persistent across all authenticated screens.
- Contains 4 tabs representing the core app sections.
- Home tab is the default selected tab and default landing page.

### 7. Profile / Settings
- View and edit personal details (name, email, phone).
- Profile confirmation screen shown after first sign-up.

## Move Types

| Type | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Light** | Small moves — a few boxes, bags, or small items. |
| **Regular** | Standard apartment or office move with typical furniture and belongings. |
| **Premium** | Large-scale or high-value moves requiring special handling, extra movers, or larger vehicles. |

## Move Categories

| Category | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| **Instant** | On-demand move request. User needs items moved as soon as possible. |
| **Scheduled** | Pre-planned move. User sets a future date/time for the move. |

## Out of Scope (This Phase)

- Driver/Mover-facing application features.
- Mobile backend infrastructure setup (relying on existing web app backend; mobile API integration to follow).
- Payment gateway integration (UI-only phase).
- In-app chat or messaging between client and mover.
- Push notification system.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** React Native with Expo (managed workflow).
- **Design Source:** Figma with Figma MCP for design-to-code context.
- **AI Coding Agent:** Claude Code for accelerated UI development.
- **Navigation:** Expo Router (file-based routing).

